{
  "texts": [
    "We implemented a graph-based generalization of the TEASAR skeletonization algorithm 43 on the L2-graph to remove short and artificial branches introduced by the L2 chunk boundaries.",
    "Skeleton calculations of neurons in MICrONS65 and FlyWire took a median of 5,996 ms and 1,171 ms (Fig. 3d), respectively, with differences again being explained by the difference in size (Fig.",
    "3e and Extended Data Fig. 4c).",
    "CAVE supports a diverse set of annotations from manual and automated sources.",
    "Every annotation is based on points in space (≥1) that serve as spatial anchors and are accompanied by a set of data entries (Fig. 4a)."
  ]
}